# Mintlify Documentation Rule

## MCP Server

- **Mintlify MCP server** is configured in Cursor at `https://sbn.mintlify.app/mcp`
- Use the MCP `search` tool to find existing documentation content before creating or editing pages.
- Use the MCP `get_page` tool to retrieve full page content by path.

## Skills

Follow the installed Mintlify skills (`.agents/skills/mintlify/`, `.agents/skills/mintlify-docs/`, `.agents/skills/mintlify-api/`) for best practices when writing or editing documentation.

## Docs Structure

- All documentation lives in `docs/` at the repository root.
- Site configuration is in `docs/docs.json`.
- Pages are `.mdx` files with YAML frontmatter (`title` and `description` required).
- New pages must be added to the `navigation` in `docs/docs.json` or they won't appear in the sidebar.
- Internal links use root-relative paths without file extensions: `/getting-started`.
- Images go in `docs/images/`.

## Auto-deploy

Mintlify auto-deploys when changes are pushed to the connected GitHub repository (`ErikLydecker/sbn`). No manual deployment steps are needed.

## Conventions

- Second-person voice ("you").
- Sentence case for headings.
- All code blocks must have language tags.
- No marketing language or filler phrases.
- Keep docs in sync with code -- when source code changes (configs, schemas, APIs), update the corresponding docs pages.
